tal legal concepts and practices and the milieu in which jurists operated. They offer entry points for exploring perennial subjects such as the professionalization of lawyers, the tangled relationship between law and morality, the role of gender in the socio-legal order, and the extent to which the ius commune can be considered an autonomous system of law.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Mai 2021) 0aCommon lawzItalyxHistoryyTo 1500vSources. 0aJurisprudencezItalyxHistoryyTo 1500vSources. 0aLawzItalyxHistoryyTo 1500vSources. 0aLaw, MedievalvSources. 7aHISTORY / Medieval.2bisacsh  aBaldus de Ubaldis.  aBartolus of Sassoferrato.  aConsilia.  aIus Commune.  aMedieval Citizenship.  aMedieval Serfdom.  aMedieval law.  aRoman Civil Law.  adowry.  ahistory of law.  amedieval Italian jurisprudence.  arule of law.1 aArmstrong, Lawrin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKirshner, Julius , eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishz978311070471608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020z9783110704518oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Englishz978311070473008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE History 2020z9783110704525oZDB-23-DEG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUTP Pilot eBook-Package 2020z978311069045340uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148753633640uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781487536336423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781487536336.jpg  a978-3-11-069045-3  UTP Pilot eBook-Package 2020b2020  a978-3-11-070471-6  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2020 Englishb2020  a978-3-11-070473-0  EBOOK PACKAGE History 2020 Eng